The design of AI agents has shifted from “black box” complexity toward transparent, file-based systems. Recently, I had the chance to dig into the internals of Claude Code, Anthropic’s new agentic tool. While it isn’t officially open-source, several deep dives into its architecture (before the inevitable DMCA takedowns) revealed a memory management system that is surprisingly elegant, strictly hierarchical, and — most interestingly — devoid of vector databases or RAG.

